cancer doctors cite risks drinking alcohol american society clinical oncology, represents many nation’s top cancer doctors, calling attention ties alcohol cancer. statement published tuesday journal clinical oncology, group cites evidence even light drinking slightly raise woman’s risk breast cancer increase common type esophageal cancer.heavy drinkers face much higher risks mouth throat cancer, cancer voice box, liver cancer and, lesser extent, colorectal cancers, group cautions.“the message not, ‘don’t drink.’ it’s, ‘if want reduce cancer risk, drink less. don’t drink, don’t start,’” said dr. noelle loconte, associate professor university wisconsin-madison lead author asco statement. “it’s different tobacco say, ‘never smoke. don’t start.’ little subtle.”other medical groups cited risks alcohol possible cause cancer. first time asco taken stand.drinking all, well heavy drinking problem drinking, rise united states affect segments society, including women, older adults, racial ethnic minorities poor, several surveys shown.yet adults, asked, identify alcohol consumption risk factor cancer, even though vast majority familiar cancer risk factors, like smoking sun exposure, recent asco survey 4,016 adults found. fewer one three adults identified alcohol risk factor cancer. (most also failed mention obesity risk factor.)the doctors’ group also calling new public health initiatives curb alcohol use, taxes restrictions ads targeting minors, like new ban alcohol advertising new york city’s subways buses slated go effect january. group likewise opposes “pink washing,” alcohol companies drape products pink ribbon enhance sales, practice opposes “given consistent evidence shows link alcohol consumption increased risk breast cancer.”for statement, asco researchers reviewed earlier published studies concluded 5.5 percent new cancers 5.8 percent cancer deaths worldwide could attributed alcohol. paper stated clearly alcohol plays causal role cancers throat neck, voice box, liver colon, well esophageal squamous cell carcinoma and, women, breast cancer.for women, one alcoholic drink day increase breast cancer risk, according report released may american institute cancer research world cancer research fund cited asco. report analyzed 119 studies, including data 12 million women quarter million breast cancer cases, concluded strong evidence alcohol consumption increases risk pre- postmenopausal cancer, drinking small glass wine beer every day — 10 grams alcohol — increases premenopausal breast cancer risk 5 percent postmenopausal risk 9 percent.“the drink, higher risk,” said dr. clifford a. hudis, chief executive asco. “it’s pretty linear dose-response.”even drink moderately, defined centers disease control one daily drink women two men, face nearly doubling risk mouth throat cancer double risk squamous cell carcinoma esophagus, compared nondrinkers. moderate drinkers also face elevated risks cancers voice box, female breast cancer colorectal cancers.the risk heavy drinkers — defined eight drinks week women 15 week men, including binge drinkers — multiples higher. heavy drinkers face roughly five times risk mouth throat cancers squamous cell esophageal cancers nondrinkers, nearly three times risk cancers voice box larynx, double risk liver cancer, well increased risks female breast cancer colorectal cancer.“if look figures, see alcohol contributing factor; certainly causal role,” dr. hudis said.the international agency research cancer, part world health organization, first classified consumption alcoholic beverages carcinogenic humans 1987, tying consumption cancers mouth, throat, voice box, esophagus liver, said susan gapstur, vice president epidemiology american cancer society.since then, said, evidence accumulated tying alcohol broader group cancers, including colorectal cancer and, women, breast cancer. recent i.a.r.c. report concluded alcohol “is cause cancers oral cavity, pharynx, larynx, esophagus, colorectum, liver female breast.” (the esophageal cancer largely specific squamous cell carcinoma.)“the story alcohol quite consistent peeled away like onion time, we’re continuing learn mechanisms involved,” dr. gapstur said. “we don’t randomized trials, sometimes start looking coherence evidence, including observational epidemiology, lab studies, mechanistic studies, begin see picture get clarity.”one way alcohol may lead cancer body metabolizes acetaldehyde, causes changes mutations dna, dr. gapstur said. formation acetaldehyde starts alcohol comes contact bacteria mouth, may explain link alcohol cancers throat, voice box esophagus, suggested.dr. anne mctiernan, scientist fred hutchinson cancer research center author one earlier reports alcohol breast cancer, said pleased oncologists focusing alcohol.“that puts weight behind this,” said. “shows they’re serious willing put name line changes policy, willing say even small amounts alcohol increase risks cancers small degree.”
trump administration guiding health shoppers agents paid insurers washington — cutting funds nonprofit groups help people obtain health insurance affordable care act, trump administration encouraging use insurance agents brokers often paid insurers help people sign up.the administration said recent bulletin “increasing partnerships” insurance agents viewed “important stakeholders” federal marketplace, consumers shopping insurance. health policy experts warned shift nonprofit groups, supposed provide impartial information, brokers agents, may receive commissions plans recommend, carries risks consumers.“insurance agents educate consumers marketplace, good thing,” said sabrina corlette, research professor georgetown university’s health policy institute. “but worry work commission therefore financial incentive steer consumers particular products, may may consumer’s best interest.”in bulletin, administration said agents brokers registered federal marketplace “get sales leads” new clients. offered tips “making marketplace participation open enrollment period,” runs dec. 15.consumers get contact information agents brokers, well nonprofit groups known navigators, clicking “find local help” healthcare.gov.from there, consumers connect service administration added year specifically connect licensed agents brokers provide immediate assistance.“get help now!” says federal website describing new service, called help demand. “a marketplace-registered agent broker contact 30 minutes less help enroll. agents’ brokers’ services generally free you. they’re usually paid insurance companies.”more 43,000 agents brokers received training certified sell health plans federal marketplace. advocates said could provide lifeline consumers confusing troubled marketplace.michael lujan, former president california association health underwriters, called agents “the unsung heroes health care marketplace.”“the trump administration set sabotage affordable care act defunding many nonprofit navigator