excuses, people: get new shingles vaccine medical researchers government health policymakers, cautious lot, normally take pains keep expectations modest they’re discussing new finding treatment.they warn studies’ limitations. point isn’t known. emphasize correlation doesn’t mean causation.so it’s startling hear prominent experts sound positively excited new shingles vaccine advisory committee centers disease control prevention approved last month.“this really sea change,” said dr. rafael harpaz, veteran shingles researcher c.d.c.dr. william schaffner, preventive disease specialist vanderbilt university school medicine, said, “this vaccine spectacular initial protection rates every age group. immune system 70- 80-year-old responds person 25 30.”“this really looks breakthrough vaccinating older adults,” agreed dr. jeffrey cohen, physician researcher national institutes health.what’s causing enthusiasm: shingrix, pharmaceutical firm glaxosmithkline intends begin shipping month. large international trials shown vaccine prevents 90 percent shingles cases, even older ages.the currently available shingles vaccine, called zostavax, prevents half shingles cases age 60 demonstrated far less effectiveness among elderly patients.yet people risk blistering disease, often intense pain, threat vision associated nerve pain sometimes last months, even years, initial rash fades.almost older americans harbor varicella zoster virus causes shingles; acquired childhood chickenpox, whether knew disease not.the virus stays dormant until, unknown reasons, erupts decades later. risk rises sharply age 50.shingles hardly minor menace. “a million cases occur united states every year,” dr. schaffner said. “if you’re fortunate enough reach 80th birthday, stand one-in-three one-in-two chance shingles.”preventing great majority cases — along risk lingering debilitating nerve pain, called postherpetic neuralgia — would represent major advance public health.so old vaccine remain market, c.d.c. committee voted make shingrix preferred vaccine recommended adults age 50 — group younger decade earlier encouraged get zostavax.the committee also recommended shingrix adults who’ve previously gotten zostavax, since smaller study people age 65 demonstrated effectiveness safety already vaccinated. food drug administration approved shingrix last month.once c.d.c.’s director endorses committee’s recommendations, agency publishes them, insurers — including medicare medicaid — start covering vaccine.“by early 2018, broadly available consumers u.s.,” said dr. thomas breuer, chief medical officer gsk vaccines. (canada also approved shingrix; awaits approval australia, japan europe.)what makes new vaccine promising, especially older adults?* provides better protection shingles start. though zostavax, introduced 2006, reduce shingles cases half (and postherpetic neuralgia two-thirds), overall rate conceals big differences age.that vaccine’s effectiveness drops 64 percent people 60s 38 percent among age 70, falls still lower people 80s.but new vaccine protects nearly well older groups middle-aged. shingrix racked 97 percent effectiveness rate adults age 50 and, separate study people age 70, prevented 90 percent shingles 70 well past age 80.“in groups elderly, often don’t maintain vigorous responses vaccines, represents extremely strong disease protection,” said dr. kathleen dooling, epidemiologist c.d.c.* shingrix’s protection appears last longer. among seniors, effectiveness zostavax wanes disappointing speed. “after 11 years, protection close zero,” dr. harpaz said.regulators don’t yet 11 years data shingrix, samples, remained effective six years longer, according gsk. greatly reduce incidence postherpetic neuralgia, too, assuming 42 million people 50s start getting vaccinated.* new vaccine may protect people compromised immune systems.a substantial number older americans suppressed immunity they’re undergoing chemotherapy transplants, h.i.v. take steroids. them, previous vaccine off-limits made weakened live virus.yet immune suppression leaves people vulnerable shingles. shingrix, recombinant vaccine made glycoprotein combination immunity boosters called adjuvants, doesn’t pose danger.the c.d.c. committee held recommending shingrix immunocompromised, gsk still running trials patients. since f.d.a. declare shingrix contraindicated approving it, get vaccine it’s available.public health advocates foresee couple potential problems.first, shingrix requires two doses, administered least two months apart. prodding older population get single shot proved tough: barely 31 percent age 60 vaccinated shingles. much harder persuade people get two shingrix injections?further, “it tends bit ouch-y vaccine,” dr. schaffner cautioned.in studies, older recipients said they’d experienced pain, redness swelling upper arms day two shot, 8.5 percent age 70 deemed symptoms uncomfortable enough interfere normal activities.about half age 70 reported systemic side effects like fatigue, fever aching joints, lasting one two days. physicians pharmacists prepare people reactions, dr. schaffner said.“if people anticipate it, they’ll cope better. they’ll take couple tylenol” — worry something seriously wrong.they may feel pocketbook pain, too. zostavax expensive adult vaccine, $140 dose (plus cost administering injection), shingrix pricier still.the 50- 65-year-old cohort, many coverage employee health plans, may find much barrier. older ages, cost matters more.medicare cover shingrix part (like predecessor), part b like flu vaccine. complicates reimbursement seeking vaccination doctors’ offices, medicare patients probably find simpler head pharmacy.but medicare recipients part d, could face co-payments.still, it’s contest: hazards shingles complications dwarf problems yet reported shingrix.“compared shingles, little arm pain day small price pay,” dr. schaffner said. “if know people who’ve illness, you’ll first line vaccine.”
war end wars doesn’t trick q. seems though city parks monuments world war world war ii. why?a. you’re imagining things. 120 world war memorials city parks. that’s almost twice number world war ii monuments, despite resounding american triumph general popularity latter conflict, mention much higher toll took soldiers united states.there reasons this. chief among shift optimism “war end wars” sobriety looming standoff soviet union. city topics mid-20th century, planning czar robert moses played role, too.world war first conflict large number american soldiers went overseas fight. 400,000 new york state fought, 10 percent american troops. war ended, seemed like every organization city wanted honor local veterans.there monuments local residents, like pleasant plains memorial, honoring veterans staten island’s fifth ward, military units, like central park’s 305th infantry memorial grove.thousands smaller remembrances also dotted urban landscape: tree planted here, plaque church there.this variety, mention sheer quantity, sit well moses, parks commissioner 1934 1960. considered many first world war monuments eyesores, sought restrict number world war ii memorials one per borough.although moses eventually softened opinion, initial stance probably dampened enthusiasm building plethora monuments.moses entirely blame; nation’s attitudes toward war changed considerably. world war ii destroyed notion “lasting peace.” classical statue angel soldier could properly reflect horrors concentration camps. many felt prudent wait enough time passed put war proper perspective.
