christians must support gun control sutherland springs, tex. — rural texas, hay, baled rolled, waits winter. corn shorn stiff yucca stands guard dusk. know country; short drive home, past places like devil’s backbone purgatory skinny cibolo creek, choked mesquite live oak. sutherland springs, family five trudges front headlights, past police cordon, shuffling, heads down, apparently headed home. call god’s country, partly beauty, partly sometimes feels like god thing here.as many small texas towns, center sutherland springs church. anything stands worst mass murder history texas, took place last sunday, killing 26 wounding least 20, this: simple, white wooden sanctuary peaked roof, next unkempt field lonesome two-lane road.now going tear down, bulldozing south texas plain, could remove sacrilege killing defenseless people sunday sermon. america’s response mass homicide come to. don’t remove killing machines put tens thousands americans graves hospital beds century, demolish first baptist church stood lonely crossroad nearly century. doomed site, rooted black soil, cries people faith act.the killer, devin patrick kelley, used ruger ar-556, 15 30-round magazines, shoot nearly 50 helpless, trapped people. weapon variant ar-15, barely distinguishable m-16, american military’s standard-issue infantry weapon. these, along handguns, weapons choice today’s mass killers.i won’t pretend religious next person, afraid call christian. like lot americans, complicated relationship faith. shouldn’t lessen sense moral obligation face blithely call new normal. fall siren call guns, unproven good-guy-with-a-gun myth, something many fellow texans indulged past days. instead, duty confront machines profiteering behind them.it easy feel numb, powerless hopeless. dead, one grimace last moment fear. survivors beloved, harsh sentence awaits. first, trauma, like amputation, something c. s. lewis wrote death wife, joy davidman, 1960. “no one ever told grief felt like fear. afraid, sensation like afraid,” lewis, catholic, wrote slender tortured memoir “a grief observed.” “the fluttering stomach, restlessness, yawning. keep swallowing.”when traumatic death strikes, common question is, “why?” second common question invariably, “where god?” last troubling is, “what god want?” cry jesus let cross darkness spread across land: “my god, god, forsaken me?”i won’t pretend know mind god, offer simple guess would say: stop killing. course killing never end, completely; imperfect creatures free will, prone sin — absence good — well beauty. categorically different allowing proliferation machines solely designed kill large numbers people quickly, machines bear semblance rifle nuclear weapon firework. sin omission — nothing — nearly bad murder itself.in recent years, time time, ar-15 one close cousins played starring role american mass shooting. las vegas shared macabre double-billing semiautomatic version russian ak-47. chattanooga. orlando. san bernardino. aurora. two like nearly always there.and reason. weapons’ quasi-military design, even unskilled hand pull trigger 40 times minute. typical hunting rifle hold several rounds. typical ar-15 magazine holds 30. least five million ar-15-type weapons nation alone. sturm, ruger & company, connecticut company made weapon used here, reported $664 million net sales last year.here texas, politicians come gone, visiting sutherland springs raw, rainy wednesday night, making empty calls prayers excuses inaction, vice president mike pence awkwardly intoned, “words fail saints heroes fall.” indeed, do. words, bereft real meaning, blow away cold north wind. appears forget purportedly deep religiosity.christianity demands action. insists protection innocent. 13th century, st. thomas aquinas justified war self-defense, also opposed killing innocent civilians. “aquinas holds causing death innocents foreseeable manner, whether intentionally indirectly,” according cambridge divinity scholar daniel h. weiss, “is never justified.”and yet 