myth artistic genius excuses abuse women away idea “separating art artist”?whenever creative type (usually man) accused mistreating people (usually women), call arises prevent pesky biographical details sneaking assessments artist’s work. hollywood players accused sexual harassment worse — harvey weinstein, james toback, kevin spacey louis c.k., name ever-expanding list — never seemed interested separating art misdeeds. we’re learning every day entertainment industry shaped abuses power. it’s time consider art been, too.these men stand accused using creative positions offend — turning film sets hunting grounds; grooming young victims acting classes; luring female colleagues close pretext networking, trap uninvited sexual situations. performances watch onscreen shaped actions. offenses affected paths artists, determining rise prominence harassed shamed work. turn, critical acclaim economic clout afforded projects worked insulate consequences behavior.this idea assessing artist’s work light biography is, critics, blasphemous. roman polanski’s 2009 arrest inspired new york times round table whether ought “separate work artists artists themselves, despite evidence reprehensible even criminal behavior.” stands useful artifact prevailing attitude question early 21st century. screenwriter critic jay parini wrote, “being artist absolutely nothing — nothing — one’s personal behavior.” mark anthony neal, african-american studies scholar duke university, put way: “let art stand itself, men stand judgment, never twain shall meet.”but mr. polanski stood charged inviting 13-year-old girl jack nicholson’s hot tub pretext photographing model, drugging raping her. twain met.a proclivity reprehensible acts built right mythos artistic genius — designation rarely extended women. historian martin jay calls “the aesthetic alibi”: art excuses crime. mr. jay writes 19th century, artistic genius “was often construed unbound nonaesthetic considerations — cognitive, ethical, whatever.” often ethical lapses afforded artists concerned mistreatment women.that tradition lives today. recently, new yorker film critic richard brody responded sexual assault accusations mr. weinstein suggesting outside information filmmakers “can illuminating,” “better film is, likelier biography fills details regarding already apparent cleareyed viewing.” that’s bizarre calculation dismisses discussions bad deeds based talent person performing them. journalist gay talese blunter dismissal anthony rapp, “rent” star accused kevin spacey preying 14. “i hate actor ruined guy’s career,” said.directors, meanwhile, justified mistreatment plain resentment women gritty artistic choice. bernardo bertolucci, director “last tango paris,” boasted chose fully inform lead actress, maria schneider, details film’s infamous butter scene “wanted reaction girl, actress.” (“i felt humiliated honest, felt little raped,” said experience.) director lars von trier whipped misogyny persona, delighting riling actresses selling stories magazines kicky evidence transgressive brilliance. auteur, celebrated tightly controlling aspects filmmaking, seems enhance reputation flaunting control women.meanwhile, entertainment industry seems quite interested conflating art artist long helps sell movie tickets. (if hollywood weren’t invested selling people behind art, oscars wouldn’t televised.) stars power brokers reflexively praised societal contributions. even they’ve accused harassment, hollywood men attempted fend charges trotting good deeds. mr. spacey cynically chose moment announce gay bid spin harrowing assault tale heartwarming coming-out one. mr. weinstein countered accusations dozens women mentioning generous contributions scholarship fund female directors. bill cosby happy confuse art personal life bellowed old fat albert catchphrase — “hey, hey hey!” — exited courtroom past summer trial sexual assault.louis c.k., one respected celebrated comedians today, built public persona simultaneously capitalizes p