new fashion hub? eastern europe 2014, magda butrym, young warsaw-based stylist-turned-fashion designer, debuted 35-piece collection floral print dresses blouses, finished cutaway detailing hints leather hand crochet.“i always wanted launch label distinctly proudly polish,” said 32-year-old designer, largely self-taught. “i wanted create clothes inspired polish craftsmanship, manufactured poland, design studio here, too. also knew going easy.”she worked number small design businesses warsaw starting brand bears name. “there buyers here, fashion week. one tell things, need get foot door. taking big risk.”historically, poland, eastern european countries like hungary romania, never considered high fashion destinations. behind scenes, however, close ties industry existed decades, factories across region quietly producing garments accessories western european luxury houses louis vuitton hugo boss.over last decade, business moved elsewhere companies hunt cheaper labor lower production costs, leaving many skilled workers without jobs. now, new generation homegrown luxury entrepreneurs building businesses take advantage craftsmanship.in hungary, contemporary women’s wear brand aeron founded 2012 eszter aron, head designer, three friends, vivien laszloffy joining business chief executive 2015. label’s philosophy, ms. laszloffy said, brand “that people recognize know budapest, way people look acne know it’s sweden.”“people say odds build brand here, rather move paris milan, actually see advantage,” said. “everyone vision minds french italian brand looks like. one imagine brand budapest yet. seize space make own.”as privately owned company, sales figures released. two women said sales doubled annually last three years, majority growth coming unexpected region: asia.after struggling gain traction west, pair looked eastward, brand’s minimalist aesthetic techno-fabrics gained appreciation. 60 percent sales come region: japan, áeron stocked major department store isetan fashion cha