thrive live decent life,” said.people may neglect pet reptiles amphibians common pets. even best environments “will result ‘controlled deprivation’,” also case caged birds rabbits, fish tanks, wrote dr. pasmans review.just many pet owners provide high standard care dogs, cats, birds fish, possible, lot effort, properly look reptiles amphibians homes, adds. instance, bearded dragons adapt rather well captivity.clifford warwick, consulting biologist exotic animal welfare lead author viewpoint journal, said can’t provide proper care don’t know many species need. even do, misinformation internet leads pet owners astray.it’s easy buy cute pet impulse, “when people find much trouble are, turn loose,” said ms. leahy.generally, limited options dealing unwanted exotic pets means many owners release them. discarded pets wreak havoc nonnative ecosystems. red-eared slider cart mississippi huge problem europe asia.and florida dealing biggest invasive species problem planet, mostly pet trade. there, iguanas destroyed concrete infrastructure burmese pythons eaten protected common species, setting disease-spreading chain reaction.despite concerns, reptile amphibian owners aren’t going disappear sooner dog, cat bird owners.in past, people summoned emotional arguments single slick-skinned exotic pets bad reputations. animals aren’t harmful harm inherent trading them.the contributors review hope heeding scientific arguments, rules reptile ownership conceived fairly.
bridge wobbles. you. that’s trouble starts. bouncy foot bridge charming — isn’t.this case brooklyn’s squibb park bridge 2014, london’s millennium bridge 2000 long list bridges throughout history became worrisomely wobbly large crowds crossed them. authorities temporarily closed squibb park millennium bridges spent millions dollars repairs.what gives?engineers expect bridges move little cars, people wind. things get dangerous, like millennium bridge opening, blame interactions moving crowds bridges, scientists suggest study published friday journal science advances.movements bridges people feed one another, igor belykh, applied mathematician georgia state university, led study, explained. step bridge, moves little bit; adjust steady yourself. on. “however bridge starts wobbling significantly, i, pedestrian, adjust gait,” said. critical number people try find balance time movements sync up, align sway bridge. that’s things get scary.researchers attributed wobbly millennium bridge phenomenon, call phase-locking. new study confirmed challenged popular belief sway gradually grew crowd size. found wobble starts suddenly, crowd exceeds critical threshold. millennium bridge, 165 people.dr. belykh colleagues described dynamic relationships using complex mathematical models — jokingly call “crash test dummies” — hope become part industry standards. using models, engineers designers may able plug details bridge potential pedestrians figure big crowd must get bridge starts wobble.what exactly causes initial wobbling, though, something researchers still trying figure out. may something might switch gait find balance, taking wider steps, moving side side lifting legs more. describe pedestrians moving manner non-smooth oscillators models.every time step, push ground one way, other. you’re bridge, push too. causes sway. respond. sways. on. imagine whole bunch crowd — hundreds non-smooth oscillators. timing steps, force put bridge important happens wobbliness.this might also explain cases wobbly bridges didn’t show visual signs crowds syncing steps, like clifton suspension bridge bristol, england, authorities limited pedestrian traffic city’s busy annual balloon fiesta. researchers currently collaborating scientists england united states see case visual signals could help orchestrate crowd movements prevent stop bridges wobbling.but then, may think twice crossing bridge. “unfortunately, study know bridges, uncomfortable become cross,” said dr. belykh.
