helped us find identity, attempt say, ‘o.k., here’s arrangement, it.’ knew authentic way us person, singing parts other.”mr. de cormier worked peter, paul mary continuing director new york choral society, position taken 1970.sometimes conduct group. sometimes conducted everyone, december 1970, taught audience philharmonic hall lincoln center sing 10 measures “beatus vir,” setting psalm 112 vivaldi.sometimes brought stars knew popular music choral society, persuaded mr. belafonte narrator first new york performance “moralities,” hans werner henze, setting “morality plays” w. h. auden based aesop’s fables. time time peter, paul mary also appeared choral society.mr. de cormier retired society 1987 later helped found vermont symphony orchestra chorus, influence new york group continues. associate conductor, michael a. ciavaglia, wrote doctoral dissertation university cincinnati college-conservatory music “the choral music robert de cormier” 2013.robert romeo de cormier jr. born jan. 7, 1922, farmingdale, n.y., long island. father teacher. mother, former selma stigberg, musician.the family moved poughkeepsie, n.y., took trumpet 7. played dance band two years colby college waterville, me., transferred university new mexico. studied music joined army world war ii.his prospects postwar career performer, least trumpet, dashed struck mortar shell europe, served infantry. wrist hurt explosion, underwent 13 operations repair it.mr. de cormier said last year considered becoming union organizer deciding music entering juilliard school.after accompanying paul robeson upper west side one night 1950, met woman would marry, louise dobbs. addition wife, survived daughter, robin; two grandchildren; two great-grandchildren. son, christopher, died 1977. mr. de cormier wife lived belmont, vt., since 1977.but used name worked broadway shows 1950s ’60s, listed credits number belafonte’s recordings name robert corman.“mccarthy responsible name change,” mr. de cormier said, referring senator joseph r. mccarthy explaining stage name way protecting mr. belafonte amid blacklisting 1950s. “i told harry didn’t want jeopardize way. many lists.” joined communist party young man, said.peter, paul mary knew mr. de cormier ms. travers, died 2009. student little red school house, progressive school greenwich village mr. de cormier taught worked mr. belafonte. “mary used wax him,” mr. stookey said last year.but mr. de cormier said expect become famous music.“i gifted students — couple pianists really excellent one composer,” said. “mary kind surprise.”
