cabernet franc finger lakes: made course last decade so, one new york state region recognized world-class wines produced.no, it’s north fork long island. often first guess. perhaps north fork’s proximity new york city hamptons reason even tepid interest wine know it. long island great potential, certainly, fine producers. region yet establish identity either quality style.the region we’re looking finger lakes new york western new york state, nearest big cities rochester syracuse.this area — deep, slender lakes look clawed earth giant prehistoric feline — defined unlikely source superb rieslings. focusing riesling bold strategy era dominated white grapes, like chardonnay sauvignon blanc. made sense diverse soils cool climate, riesling thrive many grapes often struggle ripen.it often united states decisions grapes plant motivated sound viticultural reasons commercial concerns. marketers looking wine tempt masses would settle riesling, critically adored grape difficulty achieving clear identity consumers, even, paradoxically, become popular united states.for finger lakes, though, sound decision. critical acclaim rieslings fed growth production arrival new producers.by 2011, last year new york kept records grape acreage, riesling far region’s planted white vinifera grapes, european species accounts familiar fine-wine grapes. even so, region still many acres hybrid native american grapes, like concord niagara, legacy history producer cheap fortified wines small wineries bulk business selling directly visitors.still, regions world flourish one signature wine. long riesling prospered finger lakes, winemakers debated red counterpart ought be.i’ve charming pinot noirs, made fresh, delicate style rather opulent fruit. i’ve intriguing teroldegos blaufränkisches. yet consistently good distinctive reds i’ve finger lakes cabernet francs.in last five years so, seen cabernet francs region. lot — cab franc acreage accounts less third riesling acreage — enough notice.as riesling, focusing cab franc marketing no-brainer. it’s cabernet, one without clear identity name recognition. easy path necessarily best path, true riesling, maybe cabernet franc, too, makes sense.seeking deeper understanding finger lakes cabernet franc, wine panel recently tasted 20 bottles primarily 2014 ’15 vintages, one ’16 thrown in. tasting, florence fabricant joined christy frank — who, husband, owns copake wine works columbia county, n.y. — thomas pastuszak, wine director nomad.thomas wife, jessica brown, also happen small finger lakes label, terrassen cellars, makes cabernet franc. tasting coordinator, bernard kirsch, unaware connection included bottle blind tasting. avoid appearance conflict interest, include rankings.as tasted 20 bottles, clear profile finger lakes cabernet franc emerged. wines pale color, savory spicy, sweetly fruity. indeed, fruit flavor tended toward tart end spectrum, leavened herbal mineral touches.these wines spoke plainly cool-climate viticulture, phrase often bandied regions little claim it. yet true description conditions finger lakes, alcohol levels occasionally rise 13 percent, compared 14 percent 15 percent seen regularly california. best cabernet francs light- medium-bodied almost delicate textures lively acidity, sort would go especially well thanksgiving table.“people looking food-friendly wines,” thomas said. “cool-climate cabernet franc appeal seeking mineral-driven, acid-driven, firmly tannic wines.”it’s certainly lovely, desirable style, though perhaps mainstream american yet.“up copake, lot people want something local,” christy said. “but also want something that’s big rich, it’s fine line.”as sommelier, thomas tried pique customers’ interest nomad’s excellent selection finger lakes wines.“i used say, ‘think lighter version cabernet sauvignon,’” said. “now say, ‘a spicier version pinot noir.’ it’s successful terms peoples’ expectations.”our top wine, 2014 lakewood vineyards, epitomized prevailing finger lakes style. wine fresh, al