cars lose spare tire leaner ride, could cost list items longer expect see new car — once-common features like metal ignition key, ashtray vent window swings open — may soon adding spare tire.already, nearly third 2017 models offered united states come outfitted save-the-day spare standard equipment, according recent study aaa.in truth, extinction spare tire happening, gradually, years. full-size spares gave way space-saving “doughnut” versions sometimes spot vehicles traveling worrying speeds. they, turn, yielding under-floor real estate tire all.the elimination spare automakers entirely abandonment good sense severe example cost-cutting; fact, benefit drivers. primary goal weight reduction, crucial factor meeting fuel economy standards.removing substantial amount rubber steel — 40 pounds, according industry experts — along jack lug wrench big win engineers conditioned shave ounces wherever possible. appealing may skip doughnut lose little weight, disappearing spare cause headaches: aaa said last year answered roadside assistance calls 450,000 members whose cars spares — situation mean trip repair shop flatbed.the freedom eliminate spare tires altogether largely possible result developments tire construction technology.an increasingly popular alternative spares so-called run-flat design, new bmw models use. intended make roadside tire changes unnecessary, solution employs reinforced tire sidewall typically lets driver continue 50 miles 50 miles hour air pressure lost. costly: may necessary replace, rather simply patch, damaged tire, replacements typically priced $25 $50 higher conventional design.another alternative self-sealing tire, older solution reappearing modern form battery-powered chevrolet bolt, reduced weight translates miles per charge. designed solely electric vehicle, bolt provision carrying spare. according michelin, supplies bolt’s energy saver a/s selfseal rubber, extra cost self-sealing tire — continue road even nail tread — $33 compared conventional tires size.but models losing spare without benefit run-flat self-sealing rubber, instead including conventional tires leak repair kit — packaged aerosol used conjunction small air compressor powered car’s battery.such kits skim weight skipping tire, limited abilities deal road hazard serious nail hole tire’s tread section. larger tear tire — something happen modern low-profile tires meet pothole — damage sidewall wheel rim fixed leak kit. sealants, usually one-time use devices, finite shelf life — usually four eight years, aaa said — cost $40 replace.even leak sealant kit gets back road hurry minor puncture, could complicate permanent repair. affixing internal patch sealant used requires thorough cleanup goo inside, said tom carter, technical communications director michelin.for car owner — certainly renters might know getting — best way prevent unpleasant middle-of-the-night surprise check spare sure holds air. there’s sealant kit instead, read owner’s manual (which may dvd available car’s display screen) learn use it.in cases, greater peace mind available automakers.for instance, although mainstream versions 2017 honda civic come factory space-saver spares, civic si not. spare wheel kit, including jack tools, available honda dealers accessory civic si suggested retail price $254. tire, must purchased separately, runs $115 sources like tirerack.com.bmw offers compact spare kit — including jack wrench — many x series sport utility vehicles 5 7 series sedans. cases, it’s $150 option ordering car, though models conventional tires free. sport utility models, compact spare fits entirely within compartment rear floor, sedans juts high, meaning floor panel cannot lie flat.not surprisingly, independent online retailers also emerged fill hole. buyers make sure compare prices dealership determine storage spot car tire secured. designers work smooth airflow car fuel-economy improvements, compartments going away, too.the disappearance spare tire might exercise efficiency. may sociological statement. survey aaa found 20 percent drivers know change flat tire, rise roadside assistance coverage new cars, number unlikely shrink.the era cars proudly displaying spare tire mounted front fender rear bumper — standby prewar classics — long gone, tradition suburban dads gathering inspect neighbor’s new purchase may undergo major change.instead crowding around front end see what’s hood, perhaps they’ll checking trunk see it’s got spare.
asian-american cuisine’s rise, triumph plate, egg looks like eye plucked baby dragon. yolk green-black smoked glass, gray, nearly calcified halo, trapped oval wobbling amber emitting faintest whiff brimstone.so begins $285, 19-course tasting menu benu san francisco. egg traditional chinese snack, often called (poetically, inaccurately) 1,000-year-old egg, preserved weeks months lye slaked lime, salt tea. it’s sold street vendors, tossed stir-fries scattered congee throughout china, parts southeast asia world’s chinatowns. billion people, utterly commonplace food.but present amuse-bouche one acclaimed fine-dining restaurants united states, predominantly non-asian clientele, radical. despite america’s long, complicated love affair asian cooking, hard imagine food, alien western culinary ideals appearance, aroma, flavor texture, served kind setting, let alone embraced, decade ago.this, though, new american palate. nation beholden old world traditions early settlers; crave ingredients farther shores. briny rush soy; ginger’s low burn; pickled cabbage heady funk close rot. vinegar applied everything. fish sauce like underbelly sea. palm sugar, velvet cane sugar’s silk. coconut milk slowing tongue. smoky black cardamom menthol aftermath. sichuan peppercorns paralyze lips turn speech burr, thai bird chilies immolate everything touch. fat rice grains cling, scoop hands. (as child raised filipino-american household, bewildered commercials uncle ben’s rice promised grains “separate, sticky,” good thing.)these american ingredients now, part movement cooking often gets filed melting-pot, free-for-all category new american cuisine. it’s specific that: food borne particular diaspora, made chefs “third culture kids,” heirs parents’ culture one raised in, thus forced create own.could call asian-american cuisine? term problematic, subsuming countries across vast region shared language single unifying religion. elides numerous divides: city countryside, aristocrats laborers, colonizers colonized — “fancy asian” “jungle asian,” comedian ali wong puts it. (she’s speaking specifically east southeast asians, followed similar patterns immigration u.s. primary focus piece.) yoke two origins, also read impugning loyalties code “less fully american.” asked american chefs asian heritage whether cooking could considered asian-american cuisine, always pause, sometimes sigh.but happens america: borders blur. aren’t many — americans asian descent 6 percent population, legacy decades immigration quotas denial citizenship — find common cause neighbors. term asian-american imposed us, like “yellow peril” late 19th century “oriental”; coined 1960s yuji ichioka, california-born historian civil rights activist, give us political voice. call kind cooking american, something lost.the rise contemporary asian-american cuisine began korean-american chef david chang’s momofuku noodle bar, opened new york 2004 followed four years later fellow korean-american chef roy choi’s kogi bbq truck los angeles. approach cooking typically, reductively, framed east-meets-west marriage big flavors elevated (i.e., french) technique — every asian cuisine hellbent storming palate (some, like cantonese, are, fact, renowned subtlety); culinary refinement proprietary west.but history asian-american cuisine goes back that, first tearooms banquet halls set chinese immigrants came seek fortune gold rush california 1850s. end 19th century, despite congress’s passage chinese exclusion act 1882 attempts condemn san francisco’s chinatown threat american way life — “in quarters civilization white race ceases,” declared pamphlet published workingmen’s party california 1880 — cantonese restaurants rage new york. food cheap fast, swiftly stir-fried woks, technique remained mystery decades west. (one journalist, touring chinatown kitchen 1880, wonder “the funny little things saw bottom deep earthen jar rat’s-tails skinned.”)when outsiders came flocking 1890s, chinese chefs altered invented dishes please them. less concession calculation, capitalizing opportunity. work immigrants — food arts — always dogged accusations impurity inauthenticity, suggesting one standard, preserved amber, dish writer artist roots another country say. it’s specious argument, born culture insufficient bona fides speak it. (immigrants always asked show papers, ways one.) history food, like history man, series adaptations, environment circumstance. recipes aren’t static. immigrant cooks, often living poverty, always made what’s hand, like japanese-americans rounded shipped internment camps second world war, improvised rice balls rations spam, korean filipino-americans who, survived canned goods aftermath war, eked household budgets deploying hot dogs kimbap banana-ketchup spaghetti.sometimes nostalgia kind food difficult convey don’t share history. bad saint, filipino restaurant washington, d.c., chef tom cunanan makes adobo pig tails, cheap, snubbed part animal treasured depression-era filipino immigrants working california labor camps. diep tran, vietnamese-american chef good girl dinette los angeles, told wishes could serve breakfast nothing baguette accompanied condensed milk diluted hot water, dipping. “it’s refugee food,” said. “proustian, kind like spam. people get upset; think they’re ripped off.”almost every asian-american chef spoke — late 20s early 40s — came u.s. children born parents immigrants. (in 1952, last racial barriers naturalization lifted, 1965, immigration quotas based national origin — asia, 100 visas per country per year — abolished.) almost stories neighbors alarmed smells families’ kitchens classmates recoiling lunchboxes. “i kid, farty-smelling food,” said jonathan wu, chinese-american chef nom wah tu new york. “i still feel that, i’m taking train garlic chives bag.”so chefs’ cooking, born shame, rebellion reconciliation, wistful ode imperfectly remembered never-known, idealized country. it’s mixture nostalgia resilience. wasn’t taught — certainly way cuisines traditionally taught. graduates culinary institute america hyde park, n.y., recalled little time devoted asian cooking; le cordon bleu london paris, none. one instructor took offense preeti mistry, whose indian-inflected restaurants include juhu beach club oakland, calif., likened french stew curry. another told david chang pork stock, essential tonkotsu ramen, “disgusting.”neither cooking much kinship “fusion” cuisine early 1990s, non-asian chefs like jean-georges vongerichten gray kunz began folding eastern ingredients otherwise western dishes. (“fusion” another term sits uneasily asian-american chefs. “i wouldn’t call ‘fusion,’ ” said maiko kyogoku, owner idiosyncratic bessou new york. “to describe food way? it’s extension myself.”) spirit, asian-american cooking closer american-born cuisines tangled roots: lowcountry cooking coastal south carolina, owes debt slaves west africa brought one-pot stews ingredients like okra, peanuts black-eyed peas; tex-mex, bastardization mexican food regional variant it, cultivated tejanos, descendants hispanics lived texas part mexico and, that, new spain.there’s also one cultural touchstone trauma binds asian immigrants: event national scale brought us together. part distinguishes experience immigrants people color fraught, intimate relationship countries origin u.s., foe protector, oppressor liberator, feared adored. 1899, british writer rudyard kipling urged u.s. “take white man’s burden” philippines spanish-american war:go send sons exileto serve captives’ need[...] new-caught, sullen peoples,half devil half child.this begot century american military intervention east southeast asia, history conflicting images: pearl harbor hiroshima; vietcong black pajamas american atrocities lai; teeming refugee camps smiling american g.i.s handing candy, decade decade, throngs dark-haired, starving children.any immigrant outsider first. asians america, starker sense otherness. don’t fit american binary white black. enemy; subjugated; “lesser” peoples whose scramble foothold society historically seen menace american order. yet we’ve also “good” immigrants, proving worthy american beneficence — polite, humble, grateful, willing work 20-hour days running grocery store laundry restaurant never “authentic” enough, spend every dime children’s test prep get best schools, believe promise america, work hard, become anyone. try hard enough, might even mistaken white.among children immigrants, asians america seem caught state limbo: longer beholden parents’ countries origin still grasping role american narrative. unique foreignness persists, despite presence asians american soil two centuries; none us, matter bald american accent, gone life without asked, “where from? mean, originally?” lead alienation, also liberating effect. raised two cultures — people see two heritages odds, unresolved, abeyance — learn shift them. may never feel like quite belong either, neither fully constrained. acute awareness borders (culinary well cultural) enclose exclude, allows, paradoxically, claim borderlessness, taking freely sides forge something new. asian-american chefs, seesaw obligations inheritance thrill go-it-aloneness, respecting ancestors lighting hills, manifests dishes arguably could come minds fluent two ways life.thus kaiseki niki nakayama’s n/naka, los angeles, always includes pasta course. slyly voluptuous “carbonara” abalone livers egg yolks homage tokyo-style wafu spaghetti briny pickled cod roe — it’s capped shaved truffles. tao yuan, brunswick, me., cara stadler takes tiles goat cheese made local creamery sears them, done yunnan, approximate rubing, sturdy farmer’s cheese. instead merely sprinkling cheese sugar salt, counters meatiness bright grace note mint watermelon summer’s height. caesar salad might supplanted canoe romaine, grilled hint smoke loaded dainty jako (dried baby sardines) quail eggs anchors, bessou new york. or, re-envisioned chris kajioka senia, honolulu, might mossy cliff charred cabbage — wink iceberg wedge — dusted shio kombu (shredded kelp boiled soy mirin), soaked dashi ginger, surrounded daubs heady green goddess dressing buttermilk turned gel. it’s much salad cheeky biography barbarian gates, achieving quintessence american classic asian ingredients.and asian-american cooking may expressed identified single set flavors, one thing unite disparate traditions emphasis textures. indeed, cuisine said revolutionized american food, it’s introducing unfamiliar mouth feels — crackle one doesn’t expect it, slime country that’s always shied away sensation — culinary vocabulary. justin yu, recently opened theodore rex houston, rhapsodizes “the crunch hear back head”; unrendered, gelatinous animal skin, “a fun burst fat softness”; broths barely skimmed, spoonful fat added “to coat lips.” maverick katsuya fukushima, daikaya washington, d.c., turned natto — gooey, slippery skein fermented soybeans, perfume castoff socks — earthy caramel soft-serve. like latin-american food, made americans crave heat, asian-american cuisine made “difficult” textures desirable integral food flavor itself. certain ingredients still make western diners squeamish part provocative fun.but question remains: calling kind cooking asian-american cuisine deepen contextualize understanding it, label, like speaking asian-american art fiction — way simplifying complex story making marketable cliché? danger fetishizing asian features, tendency diminishes: exotic object phenomenon, may never become recognized acknowledged more. “white chefs using ingredients saying, ‘oh, it’s strange,’ ” tin vuong, little sister los angeles, said. “it isn’t.” instead historical matrix asian culinary traditions, “young cooks see big pantry,” fukushima said. “take little bit this, little bit — there’s soul it.”chang believes food “has potential sort show we’re same.” even isn’t entirely comfortable ubiquity kimchi. “let’s say spent time asia, found recipe youtube,” said. “that’s appropriation. it’s skin color. story, pay respect means.” time, seems reductive expect asian-american chefs make food somehow reflects personal “story.” season three “top chef,” hung huynh, vietnamese-american contestant, faulted cooking technically dazzling lacked explicit reference roots. “you born vietnam,” tom colicchio, head judge, said. “i don’t see food.” (it’s hard hear echo trope inscrutable oriental, whose motives can’t deciphered, common criticism asian-americans school work overly cerebral lacking feeling.) strictures reality tv demand baring soul, asian-american chefs want work asian flavors — do, it’s always expected ways.must every italian chef make lasagna, every french chef coq au vin? anita lo, closed fine-dining restaurant annisa new york earlier year, cooked 17 years without fealty one region cultural tradition. puzzled diners. “i someone come say, ‘where’s big buddha head?’ ” said. publications request recipes submits one without asian ingredients, response often, “we really hoping something asian” — asian-ish: anything soy, apparently, do. “i send japanese, isn’t even background, works,” said.corey lee’s “benu” cookbook filled stories: grandmother foraging acorns; mother forcing drink tonic brewed deer’s antlers; father bringing home live lobster son’s birthday, joys eating tomalley (the wet gray-green paste acts lobster’s liver pancreas) buttered bread. suggest lee’s dishes, however rarefied, also deeply autobiographical. lee demurs, way novelist might, fending critic’s attempt find books correlations actual events, wanting stand alone fully imagined works art. “there’s great pressure chefs story,” said. “maybe there’s story beyond, ‘i want serve food tastes good.’ ”it’s eternal plea minority, ask judged one’s appearance rituals one’s forbears quality one’s mind powers invention. certainly country predicated right shed one’s past reborn, come nothing work way up; this, asians may among american americans. choice always exotic caricature rootlessness? philosopher slavoj zizek argues embrace “ethnic” restaurants merely “tolerance” “folklorist deprived substance”: “the ‘real other’ definition ‘patriarchal,’ ‘violent,’ never ethereal wisdom charming customs.” often asian-american chefs presumed double educators ambassadors, representing entire race, culture cuisine.in end, doesn’t matter — others, — from? no, don’t mean “originally.” mean forces made us: immigrants raised us, burdens expectations, exhortations fit never forget are; country grew in, home, taught us “other” also seems, confused, tentative way, want learn something us.for asian-american chefs, conundrum, opportunity. foods childhoods mocked rejected non-asian peers (and ashamed rebellious younger selves); accepted dilute, placating form; able command audiences clamor sensations aggressive flavors, might unnerved knew exactly putting mouths. may radical asian-american cuisine attitude informs powers it, reflecting new cockiness population historically kept quiet encouraged lay low. it’s food celebrates crunchy cartilage gelatinous ooze, openly stinks, declares: like eat. you? dare?
