onsidered non-muslims, according country’s constitution.the government quickly reversed change oath, damage done. remains unclear prompted alteration electoral oath. officials initially said change result “clerical error.”the law minister, zahid hamid, center storm. religious leaders accused blasphemy ahmadi. mr. hamid denied accusations, video message last week, emphatically stated believed muhammad god’s final prophet.but protesters calling mr. hamid fired — demand unacceptable government.mr. rizvi, virtual unknown years ago, belongs barelvi sect built reputation staunch defender country’s blasphemy laws. process amassed considerable political muscle. sermons often laced invectives profanities aimed religious minorities opponents.in september, mr. rizvi’s party entered political fray — surprise many observers — 7,000 votes, 6 percent, by-election lahore, eastern pakistan, seat vacated ouster prime minister nawaz sharif.the relatively strong showing seems emboldened mr. rizvi, used electoral oath controversy charge toward capital. ease protesters able gather near islamabad drawn attention.“any violence work advantage right wing, know it,” dawn, leading newspaper, said sunday editorial. “ government must give them.”the protesters threatened lay siege airport islamabad, railway station rawalpindi several government buildings demands met.at least 10,000 law enforcement officers poised act negotiations failed protesters tried take law hands, officials said.“the current situation cannot tolerated endlessly,” mr. cheema warned.
