putin’s bridge crimea may carry symbolism traffic kerch, crimea — looming bridge best show town.every two weeks, nikolai ench, retired sailor, wife, olga, scale scrublands kerch white toyota truck marvel colossal engineering feat inching way across strait separating crimea russian mainland.“this first time build something like russia,” said mr. ench, 67, even spent entire night august staring bridge binoculars construction workers slotted first two arches place said exactly 7:27 a.m. “we feel certain pride.”expected open traffic december 2018, $7 billion bridge project likely come freighted symbolism actual vehicles. latest series megaprojects type much beloved president vladimir v. putin.“it showing world great things do,” said ekaterina schulmann, political scientist russian presidential academy national economy public administration. “the government might able provide safety, good health care education, provide big projects. cannot bread, least circuses.”the bridge, nearly 12 miles long, carries even weightier symbolism much world considers russia’s 2014 seizure crimea illegitimate.“it signifies visible way connection crimea russia, crimea part russia, connected solid bridge — symbolic gets,” ms. schulmann said.mr. putin taken keen public interest project, least annexation black sea peninsula buoyed political fortunes domestically resurrecting image russia muscular power.in crimea, billboards bearing picture quotation lauding “historic mission” building bridge loom various potholed highways.when project first announced, however, seemed russian company wanted touch it. extraordinary engineering challenges, anything involving crimea carried risk international sanctions. even daunting, perhaps, ultimate project supervisor, known demanding boss, laying rigorous construction schedule.“the bridge difficult, scale huge tough meet deadline,” said oleg skvortsov, bridge specialist led 50-member expert advisory council. “the deadline set president, nobody wanted take risk.”into breach stepped arkady r. rotenberg, billionaire made career taking mr. putin’s pet projects. judo partner president since youth st. petersburg, mr. rotenberg also conveniently already western sanctions crimea status member mr. putin’s inner circle.there question whether mr. rotenberg volunteered pushed. official version voiced sacrifice great serving motherland, plus bridge would stand crowning construction achievement.“it seems last big project me, make money,” told daily kommersant 2015 interview. “if permit say this, contribution country’s development.”the padding involved huge government construction projects often served conduit kremlin enrich friends. notorious recent example development black sea resort city sochi 2014 winter olympics, costs mushrooming $51 billion, expensive olympics ever.boris nemtsov, politician anticorruption crusader shot dead outside kremlin 2015, estimated 15 percent olympics budget went rotenbergs, arkady brother boris. arkady rotenberg long denied exploiting friendship president personal gain.by reckoning, kerch bridge would exceptional end welter embezzlement scandals plague megaprojects. cost assembling bridge across difficult waters high deadline tight analysts believe little leeway pocketing construction funds.spanning kerch strait bridge proposed repeatedly 100 years even tried before, combination costs, war mother nature doomed every previous effort.not everyone convinced current effort succeed, either.the strait runs two mountain ranges, sending fierce winds howling narrow confines. alluvial flow various rivers carpeted seabed 80 meters fine silt. ice floes crash spring thaw — indeed, ice floe sundered german military bridge constructed world war ii — area prone earthquakes.for new bridge overcome conditions, thousands upon thousands pylons driven seabed stability. addition, various parts built using aerodynamics akin airplane wing, ensuring winds flow around structure.“all discussion geology, ice, wind, waves — would relevant 50 years ago,” said mikhail y. blinkin, director transportation policy institute moscow’s higher school economics. “now, question cost. gets expensive, all, huge advancements technology.”on hand, noted, interesting project russia’s engineering construction industry, rarely faces complicated tasks. construction actually involves twin bridges — one vehicles second due open 2019 trains. double arches rising 115 feet water allow passage ships.the huge costs involve bridge, also rail lines highways linking it, well new highway across crimea. bridge sucked significant portion budget road bridge construction throughout russia, experts said, despite official denial. government plans raise gas tax part help pay crimea’s development.“the fact bridges built, say,” said mr. skvortsov, head advisory council. “we short bridges roads. enough money, system priorities.”mr. skvortsov confessed skeptic, thinking like others modern, efficient ferry service would far cheaper practical. finished, bridge able carry 40,000 vehicles 94 trains day. cars one day 38,000 ferry transported entire month december 2016, although 305,000 transited august, peak tourist season.the russian annexation crimea changed calculations, however. ukraine severed transportation links, effectively isolating peninsula. kiev opposes bridge.some crimeans consider bridge tangible sign russia improving lot. “for 20 years everything collapsing, finally something built,” said nadezhda nesterenko, 39, postal worker also regularly monitors construction.some residents hope bridge wrench crimea provincial doldrums, even if, moment, main point appears solidifying russia’s claim peninsula.in ancient times, said mr. blinkin, transportation expert, two philosophies behind road building. romans, noted, extended highways everywhere buttress claim vast empire. contrast, scythians around upper reaches black sea avoided building roads help keep enemies out.russia adopted latter attitude centuries, mr. blinkin said. leaders like stalin shunned roads invaders could come russians could leave. hence kerch bridge departure.“politically, build physical connection,” said. “if build bridge somewhere, build highway somewhere, declare yours.”
