lahore, pakistan, smog become ‘fifth season’ lahore, pakistan — nearly two weeks, lahore, pakistan’s second-largest city, like one huge airport smokers’ lounge. abid omar’s jaw still dropped wednesday, checked air-quality monitor installed track city’s appalling pollution.it said levels dangerous particulates known pm2.5, small enough penetrate deep lungs enter bloodstream, reached 1,077 micrograms per cubic meter — 30 times pakistan’s government considers safe limit.“you see smell smoke day; actually touch filth,” said amna manan, 26-year-old manager multinational company lahore, city 11 million. “half time, i’m scared breathe in.”while delhi’s air quality generated headlines worldwide recent days, experts say air lahore rivals indian capital’s toxicity. problem limited city; 2015, according world health organization estimate, almost 60,000 pakistanis died high level fine particles air, one world’s highest death tolls air pollution.for years, pakistani environmentalists referred november, crop burning, higher emissions cold weather combine blanket lahore rest punjab province acrid smog, “fifth season.” india, punjab borders, problem seems getting worse, month reached many pakistanis calling crisis point.yet little official data sources pollution, bad air actually is. announcing new antismog policy month, punjab government admitted “scant” air quality data, saying official safety limit pm2.5 particles, 35 micrograms per cubic meter, “exceeded frequently.”naseem-ur-rehman, director punjab’s environment protection department, admitted government bought six air-quality monitors last year never installed — last week, public outcry lack data led scramble set across lahore. said department “closely monitoring situation,” thursday still releasing air-quality numbers.“this crisis data,” said ahmad rafay alam, environmental lawyer activist lahore. said six meters insufficient city size lahore, let alone punjab.in absence official information, pakistanis taken matters hands. one mr. omar, installed air monitors lahore, islamabad, peshawar karachi, lives. set twitter accounts post readings real time.mr. omar inspired experience living beijing, american embassy changed debate pollution years ago publishing air-quality readings twitter. chinese authorities ultimately prompted set dozens air monitoring stations capital across china.“i realized order air quality become national conversation way china raise awareness hazards solutions, needed numbers there,” said mr. omar, whose pakistan air quality initiative publishes data air pollution information effects health.mr. omar’s twitter updates prompted many lahore’s middle- upper-class residents buy air purifiers face masks.another activist, aysha raja, runs popular bookstore lahore, started facebook group called citizens clean air, discuss possible solutions smog problem put pressure government address it.“the political missing government side,” ms. raja said. “we public need act pressure group, watchdog, make sure something effective.”the throat-burning, eye-stinging smoke plaguing punjab created problems beyond obvious health concerns. tuesday alone, least dozen people killed road accidents linked poor visibility lahore, according police. major highways intermittently closed visibility problems.thirteen power plants run fuel oil shut since last weekend, power generation cut back four others, leading daily outages 12 hours many urban areas. one lahore hospital alone, 500 people arriving daily complaints respiratory difficulties eye irritation.“lahore looks like dystopian wasteland right now, kind like scene ‘blade runner,’” said adil ghazi, business owner.the punjab government says taken several emergency measures, including ban burning crops solid waste. says 100 people arrested crop burning hundreds factories shut proper emission-control equipment. lahore traffic police say collected $50,000 fines recent days drivers whose vehicles meet emissions standards two centers set checking commercial vehicles compliance.but environmentalists say real solution would require much serious measures: improving fuel quality, phasing fuel-guzzling cars, introducing solar renewable sources energy, planting trees large scale improving public transportation reduce number cars roads.“there lot media interest story public anger right now, emergency measures taken, long-term solution doesn’t seem priority,” mr. alam said. “the sense urgency sustained.”most important, said, government needs stop looking others blame, including india, whose crop fires pakistani environmental officials blamed worsening smog year.“no doubt smoke crop burning india big problem, let’s pretend don’t part play crisis,” mr. omar said. “the government needs acknowledge problem create awareness.”
