vietnam, bind, tries chart path u.s. china hanoi, vietnam — vietnam’s full-on war united states lasted decade. tensions northern neighbor, china, persisted thousands years — millennium direct chinese rule bloody border war 1979 recent confrontations south china sea.if geography destiny, fate vietnam expert bargaining beijing balancing superpowers.so rest world struggling reckon china’s assertive moves pacific, vietnamese, hosts year’s asia-pacific economic cooperation forum, offering guidance.“i would like give advice whole world, especially united states, must careful china,” said maj. gen. le van cuong, retired director institute strategic studies vietnamese ministry public security.like good communist soldier, general cuong pays attention details leaders’ abstruse speeches, noted president xi jinping china referred homeland’s status “great” “strong power” 26 times lengthy address last month.“xi jinping’s ambitions dangerous whole world,” general cuong said. “china uses money buy many leaders, none countries close allies, like north korea, pakistan cambodia, done well. countries close america done much better. must ask: this?”as southeast asian nations acutely aware positioned china’s backyard, vietnam worried american inattention.in name halting communism, united states sent troops indochina propped dictators elsewhere asia. american-devised security landscape also created stable environment regional economies expanded.now, mr. trump’s decision take united states trans-pacific partnership trade pact, would given 11 economies alternative chinese-led economic order, left vietnamese feeling vulnerable.“as vietnamese, always trying find way balance china’s power,” said nguyen ngoc anh, professor foreign trade university hanoi. “for us, tpp isn’t economic issue. it’s also geopolitics social issues.”ms. anh noted local liberals cheered trade pact would forced vietnam adhere international labor government accountability standards hanoi might otherwise meet.with 11 members pact agreeing proceed without united states, washington’s withdrawal — mention mr. trump’s “america first” speech apec meeting friday — leaves nations wondering best option may chinese-backed trade pacts financing deals fewer guarantees workers less official transparency.“we communist countries, people like vietnam don’t want develop way china has,” said ms. anh, studied economics soviet-era czechoslovakia. “we want follow western-oriented way.”while united states largest market vietnamese exports, vietnam’s biggest trading partner china. yet vietnam runs significant trade deficit populous neighbor, vietnamese economists worry china doesn’t play fairly.“china one countries world doesn’t observe international law many areas,” said le dang doanh, influential economist advised members vietnamese politburo trade.the vietnamese watched alarm last year beijing reacted international tribunal’s dismissal china’s expansive claims south china sea ignoring — even mocking — judgment. vietnam four governments claims resource-rich waterway conflict china’s.it hard overstate level vietnamese antipathy toward china. country public protest rare risky, large-scale demonstrations vietnam recent years chinese.but national aversion puts vietnam’s leadership bind. cannot ignore china’s growing economic magnetism. many members apec, china ranks no. 1 trading partner.in return investment project financing — roads, railways, dams, airports colossal government buildings — leaders regional economies increasingly beijing’s bidding.cambodia laos given crucial support beijing’s south china sea claims. thailand complied beijing’s demand return chinese dissidents counted haven.even philippines appeared yield, despite fact lodged successful south china sea suit hague. days mr. trump’s visit manila sunday, disclosed president rodrigo duterte ordered construction halted disputed sandbar south china sea, move widely regarded intended placate beijing.since taking office last year, mr. duterte deemed