karl katz, museum director new york israel, dies 88 karl katz, entranced art history lecture college went become founding curator israel museum, convey metropolitan museum art’s vast collection wider audiences video, play key role finding home international center photography, died wednesday manhattan. 88.his son, jonathan, said cause congestive heart failure.mr. katz also ran jewish museum manhattan; founded directed muse film television, nonprofit producer films art; and, consultant, helped plan museum jewish diaspora tel aviv, museum tolerance los angeles, hans christian andersen museum copenhagen, kiasma museum contemporary art helsinki p. t. barnum museum bridgeport, conn.from 1971 1980, mr. katz chairman special projects met, founded office film television, directed 1980 1991 commissioned nearly 50 films outside filmmakers.they included “metropolitan cats” (1984), feature depiction cats ancient egypt 19th-century paris, “don’t eat pictures” (1983), collaboration museum producers “sesame street” cookie monster restrained gobbling apples cézanne still life.“it became clear 10 years mounting exhibitions much time, effort money sunk short-lived result,” mr. katz told new york times 1984.typically, said, investments, legacy exhibitions catalog.“the logical extension fleeting experience,” said, “is film, long shelf life huge audience.”mr. katz considered serious student high school entered college contemplating career journalism theater.he appeared plays college performed sock-puppet shows children weekends, abandoned thoughts theatrical career found minor speech impediment described, without elaborating, “an unfortunate onstage experience” performing ibsen play.his epiphany 90-minute standing-room-only lecture without notes columbia art historian meyer schapiro “connections made like many synapses firing — everything psychoanalysis religion politics semiotics,” mr. katz wrote autobiography, “the exhibitionist: living museums, loving museums” (2016).“those 90 minutes sealed deal,” wrote. “i would study art history archaeology.”karl l. katz — son said middle initial stand anything — born oct. 22, 1929, brooklyn maurice katz, salesman, former rose leibovitz, active jewish zionist causes.a yeshiva student, graduated midwood high school brooklyn muddling way long island university older brother suggested transfer columbia’s school general studies, reorganized undergraduate college world war ii accommodate returning veterans.he earned bachelor’s degree art history semitic studies master’s fine arts archaeology columbia. completed doctoral thesis early hebrew manuscripts yemen never fulfilled language requirement doctorate; said could bring learn german soon holocaust.in addition son, mr. katz, lived manhattan, survived wife, former elizabeth segal, married 1978, brother, elihu.mr. katz began career recruited 1953 educator met exhibition “from land bible.” went israel archaeologist hired curator national bezalel museum, forerunner israel museum, collaborated teddy kollek, mayor jerusalem.after 13 years israel, returned new york 1969 become director jewish museum, sought reconcile liturgical agenda contemporary art.he left 1971 rejoin met chairman special projects, job held 1980. directed museum’s office film television 1991, founded muse.among documentaries company produced “degenerate art” (1993), exhibition commissioned hitler denigrate modern art; “ai weiwei: never sorry” (2012), chinese artist activist; “herb & dorothy” (2008), art collectors herbert dorothy vogel.in early 1970s, jewish museum presented exhibition curated photographer cornell capa, mr. katz persuaded mr. capa international center photography needed museum house collection. opened 1974 former mansion fifth avenue.asked 1997 times draw many professional incarnations define art, mr. katz replied: “people look art checklist; label sometimes important work art.“my sense looking art like conversation,” continued. “if it’s visual it’s visceral it’s communicative, it’s work art.”
