win battle sexes pay (hint: isn’t simple.) billie jean king united states open singles tennis title 1972, reward meager $10,000. ilie năstase, male counterpart, $25,000.ms. king fought hard equal rights and, tennis court, won. 1973, men women received prizes open. still can’t said tennis tournaments, despite ill-natured male grousing recently, equal pay still rule united states open, least.that reality overall labor market, however, women still earn less men considerable confusion reasons gender earnings gap — done eliminate it.fighting eradicate discriminatory employment practices absolutely needed, course. i’ve spent many years studying subject, research shows unequal treatment hiring work setting real may reflected unequal pay.yet also true time demands many jobs explain much pay difference, finding sobering implications. eliminating gender earnings gap require changes millions households thousands individual workplaces.even defining gender earnings gap isn’t simple: cannot reduced single number, though often expressed way. according commonly used measure adopted united states census bureau, women 2016 earned 81 cents dollar earned men, working full-time.this definition focuses annual income individual median — middle — income distribution men women. another valid option focus mean, average, earnings. measured way, earnings gap even greater. many measures.the gap larger among educated people, example, varies according occupation, often big ways. among college graduates, far larger business, finance legal careers science technology jobs. health care, larger self-employment high (think dentists) much lower professionals mainly employees (think pharmacists).what’s more, gap statistic changes life worker. typically, it’s small formal education ends employment begins, increases age. point, increases women marry begin bearing children.using data shows women earn 81 cents dollar earned men, careers recent college graduates start, gap much smaller: 92 cents male dollar. time college-educated women 40 years old, earn 73 cents.similar patterns appear using data women men earned master’s degrees business administration. immediately graduation, women earn 92 cents male dollar. decade later earn 57 cents.correcting time hours work reduces difference earnings men women doesn’t eliminate it.on face it, looks like proof disparate treatment. may seem understandable man works hours woman, earns more. compensation per hour greater, given qualifications? again, problem isn’t simple.the data shows women disproportionately seek jobs — including full-time jobs — likely mesh family responsibilities, which, part, still greater women men. so, research shows, women tend prefer jobs offer flexibility: ability shift hours work rearrange shifts accommodate emergencies home.such jobs tend predictable, fewer on-call hours less exposure weekend evening obligations. advantages negative consequence: lower earnings per hour, even number hours worked same.is unfair? maybe. isn’t always open-and-shut case. companies point flexibility often expensive — jobs others.certain job characteristics big impact gender earnings gap. looked closely issues, including extent workers are:■ subject strict deadlines time pressure■ expected direct contact workers clients■ instructed develop cooperative working relationships■ assigned work highly specific projects■ unable independently determine tasks goalsoccupations lower level characteristics (like jobs science technology) show smaller gaps, corrected hours work. occupations higher level (like finance law) greater gaps. men’s earnings tend surge fewer substitutes given worker, job must done teams clients demand specific lawyers, accountants, consultants financial advisers. differences account half gender earnings gap.these findings provide nuance explaining gap widens age greater women children. whatever changes already taken place american society, duty caring children — family members — still weighs heavily women. thought moving family-friendly nation would eliminate gap, think again. several nations, including sweden denmark, “motherhood penalty” earnings exists, even though nations generous family policies, including paid family leave subsidized child care.such considerations bring us sensitive area: domestic arrangements home, especially among couples children. personal questions. theory, gender earnings equality possible parents take amount time enjoy flexibility work.yet isn’t easy accomplish world, exists now: individual families make choices may incur high costs. classic economic standpoint, one spouse partner earn working less flexible hours, family, couple would earn money parent job, partner accepts flexible one. man certainly flexible member household — though typically not. decisions need made couple couple.reorganizing workplace — complicated undertaking — would help diminish gap. would also narrowed burdens family life shouldered equitably.in sum, gap mainly upshot two separate related forces: workplaces pay per hour work longer uncertain hours, households women assumed disproportionately large responsibilities.equality court requires level playing field home market. many battles ahead. unfortunately, need fought several levels.
