 california’s top personal income-tax rate nation’s highest.the house bill lowered limit mortgage-interest deduction new home purchases $1 million debt $500,000. move would affect fewer 3 percent mortgage holders nationally, four metropolitan areas united states half homes priced $500,000. four california. (the senate bill keeps limit $1 million.)also, state benefits itemized deductions, bills limit, many cases discourage, increasing standard deduction. economic models suggest bulk millions families would face tax increases legislation itemize deductions.more third californians itemize deductions, according data compiled pew charitable trusts; average benefit deductions nearly $37,000 2015.california state whose voters would lose deductions tax bill. according analysis tax foundation, independent think tank, six states — california, new york, new jersey, illinois, texas pennsylvania — claim half total amount deducted state local taxes.
