egon schiele still racy some, nearly 100 years death vienna — it’s nearly century since austrian painter egon schiele died, art — charged erotic energy usually showing little skin — still ruffles feathers.a series advertisements showing schiele’s graphically contorted bodies (with explicitly rendered private parts) didn’t make past critical eyes selling advertising space britain germany — anti-nudity restrictions facebook. artworks covered up.both schiele mentor, painter gustav klimt, died 1918, year world war austro-hungarian empire ended. 2018, museums vienna mount yearlong series exhibitions events mark centennial: “stairway klimt” begins vienna’s kunsthistorisches museum feb. 13; “egon schiele, expression lyricism” opens leopold museum feb. 23.vienna’s tourist board also working campaign celebrating big-draw exhibitions, viennese modernism general. campaign ran unusual glitch — office’s originally planned posters, featuring large schiele nudes, turned racy.according vienna tourist board spokeswoman, helena hartlauer, transport london rejected original images, citing trepidation depicting genitals public space.ms. hartlauer said modified advertisements pixelated genitals also declined. ultimately approved versions using artworks (schiele’s “seated male nude (self-portrait),” 1910, “girl orange stockings,” 1914, paintings artist, leopold museum collection), certain bits covered banner.the banner reads: “sorry, 100 years old still daring today.” modified images view bus shelters cologne building facades hamburg, and, since week, tube stops london.“we wondered, much viennese modernism bearable today?” said norbert kettner, chief executive vienna tourist board. apparently british germans, less austrians anticipated.in ways, no-nude attitudes abroad blessing disguise vienna’s campaign — since early november tourist board highlighting images public ads hashtag #derkunstihrefreiheit (#toartitsfreedom english) social media.the hashtag comes slogan “to every age art, art freedom,” still visible german facade viennese secession, exhibition venue co-founded klimt 1897 still operating today autonomous artist-run institution. controversy certainly echoes discussions took place schiele’s time. fin-de-siècle vienna, era dramatic shifts art society, many considered artist’s work pornographic. schiele’s first broader acceptance didn’t come early 1918 major exhibition secession — later year, artist succumbed spanish flu age 28.“we want show people far ahead time vienna protagonists really were,” mr. kettner said. “and also encourage audience scrutinize much really — hasn’t — changed terms openness attitudes society times.”
