saudi arabia comes hezbollah lebanon stunned nov. 4 prime minister, saad hariri, speaking saudi arabia, delivered halting resignation speech. mr. hariri said left beirut feared assassination. placed blame long-distance resignation iran main ally lebanon, hezbollah.in days since, saudi arabia accused hezbollah plotting kingdom ordered saudi citizens leave lebanon. threats top saudi officials causing new turmoil tiny country complicated sectarian politics, failed power-sharing arrangements long history foreign meddling.since arab uprisings 2011, lebanon largely avoided conflicts sweeping middle east. even war raging syria, lebanon’s much larger neighbor, generally left country unscathed. calm threatened trump administration saudi arabia sunni arab allies set sights hezbollah patron, iran.why would saudi leaders risk new conflagration? see way make common cause washington targeting hezbollah, one iran’s effective allies. president trump consistently singled iran’s support hezbollah groups washington considers terrorist organizations.but saudi arabia already overstretched. war houthi rebels yemen drags on, diplomatic dispute qatar remains stalemate, too. saudi leaders think score easy victory lebanon hezbollah, another misjudgment adds dangerous combustible moment middle east.hezbollah part lebanon’s national unity government formed late 2016 mr. hariri prime minister. iran saudi arabia — views protector lebanon’s sunni community — blessed power-sharing agreement.hezbollah agreed deal wanted avoid conflict lebanon direct energy toward syrian war, fights alongside government president bashar al-assad. leader strong ties sunni arab states west, mr. hariri provided hezbollah political cover continued dominate lebanon.the militia’s important role fighting syria made powerful ever. mr. hariri’s resignation exposes hezbollah allies lebanese government harsher united states sanctions, potential war israel even economic blockade led saudi arabia sunni arab allies, similar one imposed qatar.hezbollah, founded 1980s civil war israeli invasion, country’s dominant political military force. unrealistic saudi leaders trump administration expect supplanted popular lebanese groundswell removed foreign military force without causing catastrophic damage lebanon.saudi arabia’s new ruler, king salman, son designated heir, crown prince mohammed bin salman, pursuing far aggressive foreign policy previous saudi rulers. bolstered mr. trump’s support kingdom conflict iran. iran’s ally, mr. assad, essentially civil war syria, saudi arabia looking contain iranian influence elsewhere. lebanon tempting target.the saudis also emboldened recent outreach shiite factions iraq, especially nationalist cleric moktada al-sadr, visited kingdom july met prince mohammed. saudis hoping cultivate mr. sadr shiite leaders counterweight iranian influence iraq, especially ahead parliamentary elections next year.but saudis won’t able find sadr lebanon, political figure offer serious alternative hezbollah iranian influence shiite community.since end lebanon’s civil war 1990, hezbollah entrenched largely shiite areas southern beirut southern lebanon. iranian support, opened schools hospitals, provided business loans fielded candidates parliamentary elections. also extended military capability, deploying thousands missiles along border israel.in february 2005, rafik hariri, billionaire construction tycoon lebanon’s former prime minister, assassinated bombing beirut. death deprived lebanon prominent sunni leader — saudi arabia lost important lebanese ally. mr. hariri’s death, son saad took father’s saudi-based construction empire sunni political mantle lebanon.in summer 2006, hezbollah fought monthlong war israel, ended draw increased militia’s popularity across muslim world. early 2011, hezbollah’s standing began wane united nations tribunal indicted several members mr. hariri’s assassination.if mr. hariri’s killing first salvo proxy war iran saudi arabia lebanon, subsequent battles also go riyadh’s way.in may 2008, hezbollah broke post-civil-war vow turn weapons lebanese factions. time, lebanon mired political stalemate united states- saudi-backed government — included sunni, christian druze parties — hezbollah allies.hezbollah infuriated government decision outlawed underground fiber-optic communication network, critical success 2006 war israel. hezbollah’s leaders sent hundreds fighters largely sunni neighborhoods west beirut. overpowered sunni militiamen seized offices media outlets political rivals, including mr. hariri.hezbollah’s success alarmed sunni arab states saudi arabia toyed idea sending arab military force intervene lebanon. prince saud al-faisal, saudi foreign minister time, asked visiting american diplomat whether united states nato could provide equipment, logistics “naval air cover” assist army, according classified american diplomatic cable disclosed wikileaks. prince faisal warned washington hezbollah’s actions would lead “iranian takeover lebanon.”years later, saudi leaders organized similar force wage war yemen, houthi rebels allied iran. day mr. hariri’s resignation, front page saudi-owned pan-arab newspaper declared, “hariri departs hezbollah’s republic.” subtext clear: without prominent sunni leader, lebanon hezbollah’s full control — fair game latest battle iran.
