u, i?”“i guess not, sir. i’m sorry. really — it’s nothing personal. you’re nice man, father.”“i’m sorry, too, son,” said father lyons, voice sounding tired lonely. “i don’t answers. god works mysterious ways sometimes, suppose. let know change mind.”but change mind. stage life, c.o. didn’t mean “conscientious objector.” first two letters “coward.”later operation, lost dog tags. got back battalion, company clerk make new set. line religion, originally read “ucc” united church christ, put “none.”i still dog tags. i’ve spent 50 years wondering life would different courage take father lyons offer.
