oom bill.” crystal murillo, 23-year-old mexican-american aurora, colo., gutted trump’s election, unseated trump-supporting city councilwoman.for past year, democratic party engaged angry internal debate identity politics, often framed opposition purely class-based appeal. times, feels like progressives doomed re-litigate 2016 democratic primary forever, tearing apart trump tears republic. squint tuesday’s results, sort see synthesis emerging obama hillary clinton’s theory emerging democratic electorate — democrats win appealing coalition white professionals minorities — bernie sanders’s focus grass-roots organizing economic populism.in ways election revenge obama coalition. educated white liberals joined people color elect amazingly diverse group candidates. latina single mother, michelle de la isla, elected mayor topeka, kan. wilmot collins, refugee liberia, mayoral race helena, mont. seattle elected first lesbian mayor, jenny durkan. year liberals bludgeoned demands abandon identity politics empathize resentful trump voters, election reminder white men needn’t center political universe.yet class politics identity politics aren’t really binary, even they’re sometimes presented way. murillo, example, first person family graduate either high school college, told affordable housing central issue campaign. overall, tuesday great night economic populists. week, democratic socialists america 20 elected officials among membership. tuesday, 15 local office, including 30-year-old marine veteran lee carter, unseated republican majority whip virginia’s house delegates.ultimately, main lessons tuesday probably strategic ideological. democrats need contest every seat can, matter red. (in wake washington post’s revelations alabama senate candidate roy moore’s past sexual relationships teenagers, it’s good thing there’s already strong democrat race.) also recognize young people crucial fortunes, make easy run. one person played key role democratic victories tuesday amanda litman,