managing email multiple devices q. efficiently manage email three devices: computer, phone tablet? read, save, delete email three times, easily sync them?a. mail programs give choice two ways set account computer mobile device — either imap (internet message access protocol) standard pop (post office protocol). want keep mailbox sync across multiple devices, choose imap method.compared pop, imap newer technology managing messages handles checking mail account multiple devices much smoothly. imap, even though see mailbox mail program computer devices, imap messages actually live mail server. read, delete flag message, performing action mail server. mail apps devices see change view updated mailbox.in contrast, pop mail systems default settings download messages directly device checks time, deletes messages mail server. check mail computer gadgets, devices get deleted messages, may download newer ones — get deleted server, making mailboxes sync.as workaround, mail providers allow keep messages server without deleting automatically download, repeatedly delete message device. additionally, messages send stay sent mailbox computer device actually sending.most modern mail providers programs support imap find instructions setting imap mail accounts google’s gmail, microsoft outlook mozilla’s thunderbird program sites. apple’s icloud mail support pop uses imap default.
grab copies google emails, photos files q. decided leave google move another mail file-storage service. get mail, photos files stored google account?a. google download page use grab copies gmail messages, uploaded pictures google photos, calendars, contacts, google keep notes more. use it, log google account go takeout page; use gmail google’s “g suite” corporate services employer, talk company’s system administrator moving data.on takeout page, select google apps services use, add personal content one archive file. pictures download google photos exported format used uploaded images. move list apps services, click downward-pointing menu arrow get information exporting data particular google product.once made selections, click next button bottom page choose format archive — .zip format probably universal here, computers automatically open .zip archives. also select delivery method, including getting mail message link downloading archive, copying archive file microsoft onedrive dropbox folder.keep mind downloading data remove company’s servers. also remove google-based web activity delete google account. make sure archive need, log google account and, account preferences area, click “delete account services” link follow steps screen.
smartphones egypt bring biting humor also scrutiny new york times journalists use technology jobs personal lives? declan walsh, times’s cairo bureau chief, discussed tech he’s using.what tech important job correspondent egypt? dented, screen-cracked iphone center work. started foreign correspondent 18 years ago, kenya, carried small satchel held tape recorder, camera, address book, map perhaps shortwave radio. today squeezed thin black slab pocket.it taped interview leader hamas. shot video pictures drove across syria. helped navigate back streets cairo, hails cab ride home. hasn’t, however, replaced pen paper, although stack notebooks desk gradually shrinking. type faster times-issue 13-inch macbook air write. i’ve come realize that’s always plus: slow messy is, taking interview notes hand makes listen harder, edit notes go along.the key thing secure communications. many egyptians jail, many others risk arrest, encrypted apps like whatsapp signal become indispensable tools. egyptian police detained dozens gay people recently, called activist set interview, encrypted app. i’d called regular line, would hung up. apart that, digital lines simply better quality.the slack messaging app replacing email way times correspondents communicate editors, especially operation spread across world. might work editors london, new york hong kong, depending story time day.equally important, need know put technology away. paranoid corners middle east, pulling glowing laptop public great idea.how connectivity cairo region travel assignment? internet teeth-grindingly slow egypt, point yelling, ridiculously, screen deadline.in 2016, egypt ranked 146th 150 countries fixed broadband download speeds, according speedtest. worse country north africa war-torn libya. it’s surprising given major data cable, linking hundreds millions users, passes one sleepy egyptian village. problem stems lack investment telecommunications infrastructure locally since arab spring 2011 stifling state monopolies.we get around dongles connected 4g cellphone network, better, perfect. conflict zones like libya, covered offensive islamic state last year, turn bgan satellite data terminal thuraya satellite phone.but increasingly least patchy cellphone coverage even dangerous places, battle aleppo, syria, last year. brings immediacy found jarring: power facetime mom, instance, battlefront. feels normal, choices dictated less technology simply feels right.are egyptians joined hip smartphones? egyptians adore smartphones. people crazy-looking cases range dramatic ringtones — quranic verses conservatives, melodramatic pop tunes everyone else. lionel richie’s “hello” anything celine dion popular.the flip side smartphone mania also inspires deep paranoia among police ordinary citizens, known popularly “honorable citizens.” know people who’ve threatened arrest taking photo suez canal (after pyramids, one egypt’s famous features). photographer friend admonished “honorable citizen” trying take photo nile phone. accused spy.what favorite apps gadgets egypt? people facebook using google uber?egypt largest community facebook users arab world. it’s huge part many people’s lives, time public square dramatically shrinking. since president abdel fattah el-sisi came power 2013, protest outlawed news media largely thrall government. people turn social media talk politics, mock leaders hunt independent news. mr. sisi makes slip-up television, unfailingly flurry mocking memes flying facebook within hours. funny, dark — jokes country’s pitiful human rights record, instance.it’s western apps. anghami arab version spotify, souq.com big online retailer (and bought amazon year), there’s host apps tell pious muslims pray help read quran.on streets cairo, uber careem, ride-sharing app concentrates middle east, slugging market share. result, cab rides ridiculously cheap — dollars cross town.how egyptian government treat tech like social media western apps?with wariness frequent hostility.egyptian officials closely monitor facebook, twitter social media sites, posting irreverent comment land user court jail. young army conscript serving three-year sentence posting photo mr. sisi pair mickey mouse ears. since may, government banned 400 websites, including human rights watch, egyptian news site mada masr and, bizarrely, medium. earlier year, discovered security services seeking access real-time information ride-sharing customers — known inside uber “god view” — uber careem apps.all told, it’s pretty grim picture.beyond job, tech product love using daily life right why?i love bose noise-canceling bluetooth headphones, satisfying tech product i’ve started using one cancels rest. smart little alarm clock french designer philippe tabet sits bedside table, means longer need smartphone wake up.with phone banished another room, can’t mindlessly scroll twitter instagram 8 o’clock morning, enjoy tiny window mental peace. times editors need urgently, still call land line. sometimes, old-fashioned tech best.
