way wind blows q. wind turbines generate electricity seem three blades, sometimes two. few?a. many 90 percent turbines use three blades. experiments still underway determine number blades works best terms efficiency, durability economy.when wind shifts, three-blade design minimizes vibration “chatter.” two-blade system subject considerable chatter blades horizontal position, associated wear tear turbine. chatter sometimes audible.a design one blade would actually aerodynamically efficient, single blade would move fast, producing objectionable noise, wears assembly quickly.adding fourth blade increases energy production small percentage, added expense comparatively large.finally, many people consider three-blade turbine aesthetically pleasing design.
