could allergic additives food drugs? kammy eisenberg broke hives last december, attributed stress. rash persisted, ms. eisenberg covered hives “from head toe” eight months.“it everywhere,” said ms. eisenberg, 52, lives atlanta. “i beyond itchy.” even powerful drugs like prednisone provided moderate relief, said. “my allergist loss.”she eventually consulted dr. robert swerlick, emory university dermatologist known take difficult cases, reviewed medical record suggested since allergic sulfa drugs, might also sensitive dyes used color medications.within days, ms. eisenberg switched anti-allergy pills, contained two blue dyes, even though looked white, dye-free brand.“the day switched, 90 percent better,” ms. eisenberg said, adding, “i swallowing problem handful every day.”doctors disagree whether food additives like dyes, preservatives, stabilizers, emulsifiers substances provoke true allergic reaction. medical journals published case reports allergic responses food additives, including anaphylaxis, potentially life-threatening reaction causes throat constrict. many allergists say reactions extremely rare, noting reports anecdotal rigorous double-blinded studies found evidence allergies food additives exist.“it’s very, rare see hives chemical that’s food additive, small molecules typically don’t trigger allergic reactions,” said dr. scott sicherer, professor pediatrics, allergy immunology icahn school medicine mount sinai. “no one’s saying doesn’t happen, reports literature handfuls — they’re thousands.”in 1986, however, dozen deaths linked severe allergic reactions sulfite preservatives used prevent green vegetables turning brown, food drug administration banned restaurants using sulfites raw fruits vegetables.the agency also requires foods containing yellow dye no. 5 list color label, saying dye cause hives rare cases, estimated “fewer one 10,000 people.”in recent years, however, consumer demand natural foods risen, food manufacturers replacing synthetic additives natural ones derived plants, insects animal products. natural substances likely provoke allergic reaction contain proteins immune systems might react to, said dr. ronald simon, allergist immunologist scripps clinic carmel valley san diego, reviewed literature uptodate, clinical information resource used doctors.these natural additives include substances like red food dye called carmine cochineal extract, made insects; yellow dye made fruit annatto tree; psyllium, source dietary fiber derived seed husks; guar gum, made bean used binder emulsifier food drugs. implicated rare cases anaphylaxis.allergic reactions also reported carrageenin, thickener derived seaweed; jelling agent pectin; gelatin; mycoprotein/, fermented fungus used meat substitute marketed brand name quorn.our immune system recognizes natural proteins, dr. simon said, “because evolved protect us invading organisms recognize protein structures fungi bacteria cancer cells.” said immune system less likely recognize synthetic additive. (dr. simon acknowledged served consultant food additives international association color manufacturers.)dr. swerlick, dermatologist treated ms. eisenberg, agreed reactions synthetic additives rare well understood, making even difficult identify. 2013 paper, described 11 patients seen five-year period, came chronic skin disorders cleared significantly drugs containing coloring replaced dye-free medications. (skeptics say hives generally come go proof removal dyes caused patients’ skin clear.)each dr. swerlick’s cases slightly different, said, “a bit detective work.” one 61-year-old patient chronic skin problems hand, rash flared suddenly, shortly refilled prescription diabetes pills noticed color changed off-white dark purple. new pills, turned out, contained blue dye. another patient, 42-year-old man, suffered rash almost year noticed resolved went vacation left toothpaste, contained blue dye, home.many patients “a drug allergy list that’s 20 drugs long,” dr. swerlick said. “you realize can’t allergic medications. must something common them, like dye. that’s one clues.”he said people concerned dye additives watch reactions items contain food coloring, red velvet cake drinks like powerade crystal light. patients look ingredients prescription nonprescription drugs reading label using online resource daily med.unlike severe allergic reactions food, like peanuts, occur immediately, reactions additives tend delayed several hours even days, making difficult trace, said, good diagnostic tools identifying food additive allergies. one hint may allergy additive develop reaction prepared product restaurant item, even though tolerate food make home.“there’s reason skeptical,” dr. swerlick said. “but think allergy community historically equated absence proof proof absence.”
