unlocking secrets microbiome modern technology making possible medical scientists analyze inhabitants innards people probably would rather know about. resulting information could one day save health even life.i’m referring trillions bacteria, viruses fungi inhabit virtually every body part, including tissues thought sterile. together, make human microbiome represent perhaps promising yet challenging task modern medicine: determining normal microscopic inhabitants every organ knowing restore proper balance organisms disrupted.proof principle, scientists call it, already established sometimes devastating intestinal infection bacterium clostridium difficile. infection, popularly called c. diff, often occurs potent antibiotics wipe normal bacterial inhabitants gut otherwise keep check.when else fails clear recurrent c. diff infection, treatment fecal transplant healthy gut presumed contain bacteria suppress c. diff activity often highly effective, cure rate excess 90 percent.under auspices national institutes health, large team scientists engaged creating “normal” microbiological road map following tissues: gastrointestinal tract, oral cavity, skin, airways, urogenital tract, blood eye. effort, called human microbiome project, takes advantage new technology rapidly analyze large samples genetic material, making possible identify organisms present tissues.depending body site, anywhere 20 percent 60 percent organisms make microbiota cannot cultured identified older, traditional techniques used microbiologists.if institutes’ five-year project succeeds defining changes microbiome associated disease, potential transform medicine, assuming ways found correct microbial distortions affected tissues.here demonstration projects already underway:skin: dr. martin j. blaser, microbiologist director human microbiome program new york university school medicine, directing examination organisms skin 75 people without psoriasis, checking whether agents used treat condition adversely alter microbiome.vagina: jacques ravel university maryland school medicine larry j. forney university idaho studying 200 women determine microbial changes may result common difficult-to-control infection called bacterial vaginosis, afflicts 20 million american women childbearing age.blood: washington university st. louis, dr. gregory a. storch, specialist pediatric infectious disease, colleagues examining role viruses immune system blood respiratory gastrointestinal tracts children develop serious fevers result 20 million visits year hospital emergency rooms.gastrointestinal tract: claire m. fraser-liggett, microbiologist, dr. alan r. shuldiner, geneticist, university maryland school medicine, exploring microbiome affects body’s use energy development obesity.previous studies already found differences gut microbiota lean obese adults. also evidence typical high-calorie american diet rich sugar, meats processed foods may adversely affect balance microbes gut foster extraction absorption excess calories food.a diet heavily based plants — is, fruits vegetables — may result microbiome containing wider range healthful organisms. studies, mice microbiota preconditioned typical american diet respond healthfully plant-based diet.compared lean mice, obese mice 50 percent reduction organisms called bacteroidetes proportional increase firmicutes, lean mice get fat given fecal transplants obese mice. similar shift observed people, distorted ratio organisms shown reverse people lose weight following bariatric surgery.there also evidence microbes residing gut affect distant sites influence person’s immune responses. indirect action suggested possible mechanism behind rheumatoid arthritis. mice, certain bacteria gut shown foster production antibodies attack joints, resulting joint destruction typical rheumatoid arthritis.similarly, studies suggested role gut microbiota risk developing neuropsychiatric illnesses like schizophrenia, obsessive-compulsive disorder, attention deficit hyperactivity disorder, autism even chronic fatigue syndrome. researchers suggested genetically susceptible people, altered microbes gut may disrupt blood-brain barrier, leading production antibodies adversely affect normal brain development.among challenges elucidating microbiome’s role health disease determining whether changes found microorganisms inhabiting various organs cause effect. already known microbiota people various health problems based observation, making difficult say came first: disease disrupted microbiota.animal studies like mentioned clue proof similar effect people. therapeutic studies underway completed, people conditions thought influenced microbiome choice currently rely possible treatments suggested animal research preliminary human studies.for example, people irritable bowel syndrome, inflammatory bowel disease, allergic disorders infections drug-resistant organisms may benefit taking probiotics, though probiotics sold health food drugstores may ineffective. may necessary tailor-make remedy condition even patient.meanwhile, people interested fostering health-promoting array gut microorganisms consider shifting diet heavily based meats, carbohydrates processed foods one emphasizes plants. dr. jeffrey gordon, genomics specialist washington university school medicine, told times last year, “the nutritional value food influenced part microbial community encounters food.”
