table, brain appeared normal boston — brain arrived april, delivered basement hospital without ceremony, like others. differences one — important, notorious.it went lab outside city, instead one boston, examinations performed days, less likely attract attention way. instead carried service entrance, ushered secretly underground tunnel system. brain given pseudonym, three people knew identify it.other that, brain came alone disconnected past, unattached celebrity. sordid details man’s rise fall, speculation went wrong, debate justice — left behind others assess.it brain, large small, deformed extraordinary appearance, oblong gelatinous coil weighing 1,573 grams, three half pounds, carved skull 27-year-old man. coroner took special care, arrived hours later near-perfect condition.“they handled everything beautifully,” neuropathologist said.the laboratory 30-minute drive prison man hanged night two earlier. name familiar scientists, people throughout new england many around country. brain 30 miles north man recently worked, foxborough, mass.they expected normal brain man’s age.“i didn’t equate behavior disease,” neuropathologist said. “i thought that’s was.”on table, brain appeared healthy. meninges, layers translucent membranes coat protect brain, still enveloped it. brain healthy sheen.the brain sliced sheaths, maybe half-inch time, starting front. first inkling came another 27-year-old brain. even naked eye, cross sections substantial gaps tissues — fluid-filled ventricles expanded brain tissue shrank. cross section healthy 27-year-old brain looks robust, fleshy. one hollowed boomerang-shaped caverns.“the reason skull grows make room growing brain,” neuropathologist explained. “everything packed really tightly. nature doesn’t leave gaps.”the septum pellucidum, small membrane two halves brain, atrophied point looked withered fragile, even perforated. neuropathologist later went look others similar condition, youngest comparable example 46-year-old boxer.the fornix, c-shaped bundle nerves, similarly deteriorated, stripped relative heft. hippocampus, too. even famously diseased brains neuropathologist explored, men died decades later, obvious signs destruction examined naked eye.but microscope could disease diagnosed certainty. wafer-like tissues immunostained, using antibodies designed discolor specific protein — case, tau, clumps spreads, killing brain cells. full scope damage apparent.tau, stained brown, appeared like bursts fireworks frontal cortex, part brain controls decision making, impulse inhibition. neuropathologist could see spreading brain. amygdala, part brain regulates emotions like fear anxiety, temporal lobe. spotted “a perfect demonstration” lesions around tiny blood vessels, telltale sign. found previous microhemorrhages astrocytic scarring around ventricles.she declared case stage 3 scale severity, goes 1 4. damage seen anyone age. among hundreds brains examined graded, median age stage 3 brain profession 67. one 27.what made brain extraordinary, purpose science, extent damage, singular cause. brains kind damage sustained lifetime problems, too, strokes diseases, like alzheimer’s. samples muddled, everything found connected one particular disease.this one looked lifted pages textbook devoted one disease.“it’s rare us get brain person young good shape,” neuropathologist said. “it classic case. tells us lot disease.”the brain longer brain, function form, sliced pieces. pieces numbered, archived stored. scientists still study it, probably years, perfect, fascinating specimen.the neuropathologist closest associates kept months, though, man’s family agreed let results go public. september, news came headlines returned, neuropathologist interviews. released short statement confirming results examination.“i didn’t want contribute sensationalism,” said.but science cannot advance without cumulative power research, university ballroom thursday, front 150 neurologists, pathologists scientists.she stood dark put powerpoint presentation screen, several dozen slides images showing immensely atrophied young brain, mind former star field also convicted murderer.“he beautiful pathology, call beautiful,” neuropathologist said earlier.the particulars damage neuropathologist detailed — tangled tau proteins, battered frontal cortex, shrunken tissues enlarged ventricles — long become familiar paying attention brain science. things threaten long-term future industry man worked.this job faces scrutiny — microscope darkened labs scientific presentations academic conferences.“it’s scientifically interesting,” neuropathologist said. “to me, it’s fascinating brain.”
